data.title: Michael Joseph “MJ” Andrews II (1893-1956) – Find...
data.meta_description: M.J. was born and raised in Cleveland by immigrant Slovak parents.  He and his wife Pauline were the owners Andrews Hardware and lived at 9319 Dunlap Ave.  Before that, he worked as a pinstriper for Peerless Motorcars, then located at E 93rd St and Quincy Ave.  He used those skills to custom decorate many family items....
